VERIFICATION TOOLS AND INTEGRATION SURFACES ARE PERMISSIVELY LICENSED.

Trust in AI Identity evidence must never require trusting AI Identity.
Anything a relying party needs in order to independently verify our records
— and anything a producer needs in order to integrate with them — carries
its own permissive license in its directory, which governs over this file:

  cli/                          MIT         Offline verifier + audit review CLI
                                            (ships inside every Case File bundle)
  sdk/langchain/                MIT         LangChain SDK
  CPEX OCSF audit plugin        Apache-2.0  Contributed upstream to IBM's CPEX
                                            gateway; licensed per that project

Record formats follow the open standards they implement: OCSF schema
contributions live upstream in ocsf/ocsf-schema (Apache-2.0), and exported
evidence bundles are documented, self-contained, and verifiable with the
MIT-licensed CLI above.

